Token.Abstract: The WSCKeychainManagerDelegate protocol defines optional methods for managing operations involving the deleting, setting, searching, etc. of keychains. When you use an WSCKeychainManager object to initiate a delete, set, search operations, the keychain manager asks its delegate whether the operation should begin at all and whether it should proceed when an error occurs.
Asks the delegate whether the specified keychain should be deleted.

Parameter.Name: _KeychainManager
Parameter.Abstract: The keychain manager that attempted to delete the specified keychain.

Parameter.Name: _Keychain
Parameter.Abstract: The keychain that the keychain manager tried to delete.

ReturnValue.Abstract: YES if the specified keychain should be deleted or NO if it should not be deleted.

Token.Abstract: Asks the delegate if the operation should continue after an error occurs while deleting the specified keychain.

Parameter.Name: _KeychainManager
Parameter.Abstract: The keychain manager that attempted to delete the specified keychain.

Parameter.Name: _Error
Parameter.Abstract: The error that occurred while attempting to delete the specified keychain.

Parameter.Name: _Keychain
Parameter.Abstract: The keychain that the keychain manager tried to delete.

ReturnValue.Abstract: YES if the operation should proceed or NO if it should be aborted. If you do not implement this method, the keychain manager assumes a response of NO.
